За новооткриващ се Азиатски ресторант в Мол Парадайс, бихме желали да присъединим към нашият екип, позитивни и амбициозни личности, с висока професионална етика и страст към постигане на най-високите стандарти в професията. 

Задължения:

•Осигурява качествена и навреме издадена храна спазвайки вътрешно фирмените стандарти и инструкции.
•Отговаря за правилното съхранение и срок на годност на продуктите.
•Отговаря за правилното приготвяне на храната, като стриктно спазва стандарта за приготвяне и издаване на храна.
•Отлично познава състава, начина и времето на приготвяне на ястията, както и външния им вид
•Правилно експлоатира материалната база, инвентар и съоръжения в кухнята.
•Поддържа високо ниво на хигиена на работното си място
•Спазва Правилника за вътрешния ред

Изисквания:

•Умение за работа в екип;
•Умение за самостоятелна работа;
•Енергичност;
•Сръчност;
•Бързина;
•Организираност;
•Мотивация за работа;

Нашето предложение:

•Фирмено обучение;
•Възможност за настаняване при специални условия;
•Работа на смени;
•Атрактивно и редовно заплащане;
•Работа в реална, динамична среда сред млад екип;
•Възможност за развитие;

Ако проявявате интерес кандидатствайте с автобиография с актуална снимка.
Ще се свържем само с одобрените за интервю кандидати.
Всички кандидатури ще бъдат разглеждани при пълна конфиденциалност.

We are looking for someone who is familiar with the terms: high availability, load balancing, scalability, redundancy. Join the team and together we will accomplish our goals, some of which are:

• Build a highly scalable distributed system;
• Expansion of our services’ reach - 4 locations on 4 continents is suitable for now, but we still have a long way to go;
• Reducing the ‘time to market’ (sometimes one week is too much);
• Increasing system uptime - 99.99% is fine, but 99.999% is much better.

The skills required are:

• 1-2 years of experience with Java/J2EE;
• Strong knowledge in multithreading programming;
• Knowledge of algorithms and data structures;
• An ability to be self-driven, self-managed, and efficient; 
• A friendly attitude - as important as the IT skills.

Knowledge and experience in any of the following would be considered an advantage:

• Dependency injection framework - Spring or any other;
• Web services - REST, hessian, thrift;
• UNIX-based operating systems - Linux, FreeBSD;
• Experience with production environments;
• Experience with messaging, relational databases;
• A solid understanding of distributed systems and multi-tiered architecture;
• NoSQL databases - MongoDB preferable;
• Cloud computing - AWS, Windows Azure;
• Performance optimizations - from page load time, through algorithms and data structures, to SQL query optimizations.

You could be the next one to join the Trader family, so go ahead and email us your CV!

We thank all applicants for their interest, but we’ll only be able to contact the ones shortlisted.

All applicants’ personal data is protected by the law and will be treated in a strict confidentiality.

Are you kееn about quality? Is your idea of the perfect job to test developers’ code? 

Trader wants you! That is, if you meet these requirements:

•1+ years of experience in Quality Assurance;
•In-depth understanding of software testing processes and techniques;
•Strong analytical and problem solving skills;
•Experience of testing web applications across different browsers and platforms
•A very good command of English and iron-strong communication skills.
•Experience with issue tracking tools such as JIRA

But wait, there's more! These are the skills that give bonus points:

•University degree in computer science or information technology;
•ISTQB or similar Quality Assurance certification;
•Experience with performance and stress testing;
•Experience with testing mobile applications.
•Experience working in Agile environment
•Basic knowledge of databases and SQL;
•Basic knowledge of JavaScript, HTML, XML, REST, SOAP
•Basic knowledge of Linux/Unix operating system;

Now let us tell you what you'll do:

•Analyze new and existing software components and requirements;
•Develop, publish and execute test plans for complex, multi-tier applications (web, iPhone, iPad, Android) throughout the entire life cycle of the software;
•Analyze test results to identify areas of concern and spot weaknesses;
•Work closely with developers following an agile development methodology;

Obviously, we require a lot, but we also offer a lot in return: 

•Cool benefits like health insurance and 22 days of paid vacation every year;
•A competitive salary;
•Support: financial, intellectual, and possibly even emotional;
•Company parties, team buildings and social events to die for;
•A video games console;
•All the training you need to acquire and develop new skills.

If all this sounds like your cup of tea, then go ahead and email us your CV!

We thank all applicants for their interest, but only those selected for an interview will be contacted. All applicants’ personal data is protected by the law and will be treated as strictly confidential.

